==Help for Windows users==
There are two ways to add command line parameters:

===The shortcut method===
*Make a shortcut to {{c|openttd.exe|}}
*Right click the shortcut and select properties. The first box should say something like this: {{c|C:\Games\openttd.exe|}}
*Put double quotes around the text: {{c|"C:\Games\openttd.exe"|}}
*Add parameters afterwards, outside the quotes: {{c|"C:\Games\openttd.exe" -m|}}
*To add modifiers, insert them one space after the parameter: {{c|"C:\Games\openttd.exe" -n 127.12.13.1|}}
*Separate multiple parameters with spaces: {{c|"C:\Games\Openttd.exe" -m -s null|}}
*When you are done, run the game using the shortcut.

===The command-line ("DOS") method===
*Start cmd.exe (the Windows command prompt). COMMAND.COM (the MS-DOS command prompt) can also be used, but it's more limited.
*Type '''cd <directory\your openttd.exe\is in\>''' and press Enter (example: '''cd C:\Program Files\OpenTTD\''').
*Type '''openttd.exe <-param1 value1 -param2 value2 ... >''' as above (but without quotes!) and press Enter.

